{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QD4X4fHGh3UUBCygrX31xq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Changes to `internal/adapters/docker/build.go`:**\n\n1. **Overrides directory hashing** — `hashBuildContext()` replaces the simple `hashBytes(dockerfileContent)`. It hashes the Dockerfile content plus all files in `.cloche/overrides/` using a deterministic sorted walk. File paths are included in the hash so renames are detected.\n\n2. **Base image digest tracking** — `parseFromImage()` extracts the FROM image from the Dockerfile. `checkBaseImageStaleness()` pulls the base image and compares its digest to the one stored as a `cloche.baseimage.digest` label on the built image. If different, triggers a rebuild.\n\n3. **Rate-limited pulls** — `shouldPullBase()` checks a timestamp file (`.cloche/.last-base-pull`) to avoid pulling more than once per hour.\n\n4. **Updated `buildImage()`** — Now accepts a `baseDigest` parameter and stores it as a label alongside the context hash. No changes to the `ImageEnsurer` interface were needed.\n\n**New tests in `build_test.go`:**\n- `TestHashBuildContext_StableWhenNothingChanges` — hash stability\n- `TestHashBuildContext_ChangesWhenOverrideFileChanges` — override file mutation\n- `TestHashBuildContext_ChangesWhenOverrideFileAdded` — new override file\n- `TestHashBuildContext_NoOverridesDir` — graceful fallback\n- `TestParseFromImage` — FROM instruction parsing (6 cases)\n- `TestShouldPullBase` — rate limiting logic (4 cases)\n- `TestCheckBaseImageStaleness_DigestMismatch` — component tests\n- `TestEnsureImage_RebuildsWhenOverrideChanges` — integration test (Docker required)\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":275,"cache_read_input_tokens":36171,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2